  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/70604368/slf4j-from-private-to-public",
  "title" : "@Slf4j from private to public",
  "body" : "<p>I know <code>lombok.extern.slf4j</code>'s <code>@Slf4j</code> annotation creates <code>private static final org.slf4j.Logger log = org.slf4j.LoggerFactory.getLogger(LogExample.class);</code></p>\n<p>But can I make this public somehow? Making the annotation to create: <code>public static final org.slf4j.Logger log = org.slf4j.LoggerFactory.getLogger(LogExample.class);</code></p>\n<p>Thanks in advance!</p>\n"
